CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 31, 1955, pg. A25, reads: "Spirit, Mind and Body - Schenley's Hi-Y Club, under the direction of Jody Harris, believes these three prerequisites build a whole person. Pictured, left to right, are, first row: James Ostrofsky, secretary; LeRoy Titus, treasurer; John Burkhart, Vince Mellinger, Van Stewart, president; Walter Sevels, chaplain, and Isaiah Polk.  Second row: Mrs. Harris, Ronald Grady, Clarence Rockamore, Stanford Williams, James Tyler, Donald Smith, Fred Bauer, Harold Smith and Sherman Lewis.  Third row: "Stan" Waters, Melvin Matetsky, Leroy Lowry, Ronald Allen, Ralph Proctor, Ronald Blow, Ronald Fowler and Clarence Rogers Jr.  Absent were Charles Nickens and Andrew Hughey. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Schenley High School Hi-Y Club holding signs for clean living, speech, scholarship, sportsmanship, including first row left to right: James Ostrofsky, LeRoy Titus, John Burkhart, Vince Mellinger, Van Stewart, Walter Sevels, and Isaiah Polk; second row: Jody Harris, Ronald Grady, Clarence Rockamore, Stanford Williams, James Tyler, Donald Smith, Fred Bauer, Harold Smith, and Sherman Lewis; third row: Stan Waters, Melvin Matetsky, Leroy Lowry, Ronald Allen, Ralph Proctor, Ronald Blow, Ronald Fowler, and Clarence Rogers Jr.
